2021</ix:nonNumeric>, Gilead Sciences, Inc., a Delaware corporation (&#8220;Gilead&#8221;), issued a press release announcing its financial results for the quarter ended September&#160;30, 2021. A copy of the press release is filed as </span><span style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline"><a style="-sec-extract:exhibit;color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline" href="exhibit991earningspressrel.htm">Exhibit 99.1</a></span><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> to this report. </span></div><div style="text-align:justify"><span><br/></span></div><div style="text-align:justify"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Gilead has presented certain financial information in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#8220;GAAP&#8221;) and also on a non-GAAP basis. Management believes this non-GAAP information is useful for investors, when considered in conjunction with Gilead&#8217;s GAAP financial statements, because management uses such information internally for its operating, budgeting and financial planning purposes. Non-GAAP information is not prepared under a comprehensive set of accounting rules and should only be used to supplement an understanding of Gilead&#8217;s operating results as reported under GAAP. Non-GAAP measures may be defined and calculated differently by other companies in the same industry.  A reconciliation between GAAP and non-GAAP financial information is provided in the tables on pages 10, 11 and 12 of the press release filed as </span><span style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline"><a style="-sec-extract:exhibit;color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline" href="exhibit991earningspressrel.htm">Exhibit </a><a style="-sec-extract:exhibit;color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline" href="exhibit991earningspressrel.htm">99.1</a></span><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> to this report.</span></div><div style="text-align:justify"><span><br/></span></div><div style="text-align:justify"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The information in Item 2.02 and Item 9.01 of this Form 8-K and Exhibit 99.1 attached hereto shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section 18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), or otherwise subject to the liabilities under that section, nor shall it be deemed incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, or the Exchange Act, regardless of any general incorporation language in such filing.</span></div><div style="text-align:justify"><span><br/></span></div><div style="margin-top:1pt;padding-left:72pt;text-indent:-72pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Section 8 - OTHER EVENTS</span></div><div style="margin-top:1pt;padding-left:72pt;text-indent:-72pt"><span><br/></span></div><div style="padding-left:72pt;text-indent:-72pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Item 8.01&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Other Events</span></div><div style="padding-left:72pt;text-indent:-72pt"><span><br/></span></div><div style="text-align:justify"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">On October 28, 2021, Gilead issued a notice of redemption for $500,000,000 aggregate principal amount of its Floating Rate Senior Notes due 2023 (the &#8220;Floating Rate Notes&#8221;) and $500,000,000 aggregate principal amount of its 0.750% Senior Notes due 2023 (the &#8220;Fixed Rate Notes&#8221;, which together with the Floating Rate Notes, are referred to as the &#8220;2023 Notes&#8221;). The redemption date for the 2023 Notes will be November 8, 2021 (the &#8220;Redemption Date&#8221;). The 2023 Notes will be redeemed at a redemption price equal to 100% of the principal amount of the 2023 Notes to be redeemed, plus accrued and unpaid interest from September 29, 2021 to, but excluding, the Redemption Date. The foregoing does not constitute a notice of redemption for the 2023 Notes.</span></div><div><span><br/></span></div><div><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New <title>Document</title></head><body><div id="ice921668a2534dc9af7299c5a8592028_1"></div><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div style="text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><img alt="gcp_primarylargea.jpg" src="gcp_primarylargea.jpg" style="height:60px;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:180px"></div><div style="margin-top:35pt;padding-right:-6.75pt;text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">GILEAD SCIENCES ANNOUNCES THIRD QUARTER 2021 FINANCIAL RESULTS</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">2 Million Patients Received Veklury (remdesivir) or Licensed Generic Remdesivir in the Third Quarter</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt;text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Biktarvy Sales Increased 20% Year-Over-Year to Record $2.3 Billion</font></div><div style="margin-top:20pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Foster City, CA, October&#160;28, 2021</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> - Gilead Sciences, Inc. (Nasdaq&#58; GILD) announced today its results of operations for the third quarter 2021. </font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8220;This was a very strong third quarter with continued positive momentum for both our commercial performance and our pipeline progress,&#8221; said Daniel O&#8217;Day, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, Gilead Sciences. &#8220;Veklury is making a significant impact as the COVID-19 pandemic continues to evolve. The dynamics of the HIV treatment market further improved and this contributed to record Biktarvy revenue. In oncology, our marketed portfolio continues to expand with four new country approvals for Trodelvy for metastatic triple-negative breast cancer, the approval of Tecartus in relapsed or refractory acute lymphoblastic leukemia and two new trial starts for magrolimab in solid tumors.&#8221;</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Third Quarter 2021 Financial Results</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Total third quarter 2021 revenue of $7.4 billion increased 13% compared to the same period in 2020,</font><font style="color:#b6b6b6;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">due to increased demand for Veklury</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (remdesivir 100 mg for injection).</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Diluted Earnings Per Share (&#8220;EPS&#8221;) increased to $2.05 for the third quarter 2021 compared to $0.29 for the same period in 2020. The increase was primarily driven by lower acquired in-process research and development (&#8220;IPR&#38;D&#8221;) expenses, higher net sales and lower unrealized losses from our equity securities.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Non-GAAP diluted EPS increased 26% to $2.65 for the third quarter 2021 compared to $2.11 for the same period in 2020, primarily due to higher operating income, partially offset by lower interest income.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">As of September&#160;30, 2021, Gilead had</font><font style="color:#b6b6b6;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">$6.8 billion of cash, cash equivalents and marketable debt securities compared to $7.9 billion as of December&#160;31, 2020.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">During the third quarter 2021, Gilead generated $3.3 billion in operating cash flow. </font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">During the third quarter 2021, Gilead made $2.5 billion in debt repayments, paid cash dividends of $900 million and utilized $145 million to repurchase common stock.</font></div><div id="ice921668a2534dc9af7299c5a8592028_4"></div><div style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Product Sales Performance</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Total third quarter 2021 product sales increased 13% to $7.4 billion compared to the same period in 2020. Total product sales excluding Veklury decreased 3% to $5.4 billion for the third quarter 2021 compared to the same period in 2020, primarily reflecting the expected loss of exclusivity of Truvada</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (emtricitabine (&#8220;FTC&#8221;) 200 mg&#47;tenofovir disoproxil fumarate 300 mg (&#8220;TDF&#8221;)) and Atripla</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (efavirenz 600 mg&#47;FTC 200 mg&#47;TDF 300mg) in the United States, partially offset by continued increased demand for Biktarvy</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (bictegravir 50 mg&#47;FTC 200 mg&#47;tenofovir alafenamide 25 mg (&#8220;TAF&#8221;)) and Trodelvy</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (sacituzumab govitecan-hziy).</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">HIV product sales decreased 8% to $4.2 billion for the third quarter 2021 compared to the same period in 2020, reflecting, as expected, the loss of exclusivity of Truvada and Atripla in the United States, as well as lower channel inventory as compared to the same period in 2020, primarily driven by pandemic-related stocking in the prior year, partially offset by higher Biktarvy demand and improved trends in the treatment market.</font></div><div Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font price.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font price.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Truvada</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">sales decreased 87% and 76% year-over-year, respectively, in the third quarter 2021, as expected, due to the loss of exclusivity in the United States in late 2020.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Hepatitis C virus (&#8220;HCV&#8221;) product sales</font><font style="color:#b6b6b6;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">decreased 8% to $429 million for the third quarter 2021 compared to the same period in 2020, primarily driven by a favorable settlement in the same period 2020 that did not repeat, fewer patient starts outside the United States, and timing of Department of Corrections purchases on a relative basis.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Hepatitis B virus (&#8220;HBV&#8221;) and hepatitis delta virus (&#8220;HDV&#8221;) product sales increased 17% to $247 million for the third quarter 2021 compared to the same period in 2020. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Vemlidy</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (TAF 25 mg) sales increased 18% in the third quarter 2021 compared to the same period in 2020, driven primarily by uptake in geographies outside the United States. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Hepcludex</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (bulevirtide) contributed $12 million in the third quarter 2021 as launch activities continued across Europe.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Cell Therapy product sales</font><font style="color:#b6b6b6;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">increased 51% to $222 million for the third quarter 2021 compared to the same period in 2020.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Yescarta</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">(axicabtagene ciloleucel) sales</font><font style="color:#b6b6b6;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">increased to $175 million in the third quarter 2021, driven by continued demand in relapsed or refractory large B-cell lymphoma (&#8220;LBCL&#8221;) and strong uptake in relapsed or refractory indolent follicular lymphoma in the United States and Europe.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Tecartus</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:7.15pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.85pt;vertical-align:baseline">&#174;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">(brexucabtagene autoleucel) sales were $47 million for the third quarter 2021, driven by increased adoption in mantle cell lymphoma in the United States and Europe.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Trodelvy</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> sales for the third quarter 2021 were $101 million, reflecting increased use for the second-line treatment of metastatic triple-negative breast cancer (&#8220;TNBC&#8221;) and metastatic urothelial cancer in the United States.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Veklury </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">sales were $1.9 billion</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">for the third quarter 2021. Sales of Veklury are generally affected by COVID-19 related rates of infections, hospitalizations and vaccinations.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Third Quarter 2021 Product Gross Margin, Operating Expenses and Tax </font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Product gross margin was 83.4% for the third quarter 2021 compared to 82.4% in the same period in 2020, driven by the reversal of a previously recorded $175 million litigation reserve following a favorable court decision, as well as lower royalty expense and change in product mix, partially offset by higher amortization of intangibles acquired from Immunomedics, Inc. and MYR GmbH (&#8220;MYR&#8221;). Non-GAAP product gross margin was 90.0% for the third quarter 2021 compared to 86.5% in the same period in 2020, driven by the reversal of the aforementioned previously recorded litigation reserve following a favorable court decision, as well as lower royalty expense and change in product mix.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Research and Development (&#8220;R&#38;D&#8221;) expenses and non-GAAP R&#38;D expenses for the third quarter 2021 were $1.1 billion compared to $1.2 billion in the same period in 2020. Lower R&#38;D expenses reflect completion or wind-down of remdesivir and inflammation related clinical programs, partially offset by increases in Trodelvy and magrolimab clinical activities.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Selling, General and Administrative (&#8220;SG&#38;A&#8221;) expenses and non-GAAP SG&#38;A expenses for the third quarter 2021 were $1.2 billion compared to $1.1 billion in the same period in 2020. The increase in SG&#38;A expenses was driven by increased promotional and marketing activities across all geographies, primarily for Trodelvy.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">The GAAP effective tax rate (&#8220;ETR&#8221;) and non-GAAP ETR for the third quarter 2021 were 24.8% and 18.9%, respectively, compared to 57.2 % and 18.4%, respectively, for the same period in 2020. </font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="margin-top:3pt;text-align:center"><font><br></font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div style="margin-bottom:9pt"><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:100.000%"><tr><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:27.390%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:37.931%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:31.379%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">October&#160;28, 2021</font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><div style="text-align:right"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">3</font></div></td></tr></table><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></div></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Key Updates Since Our Last Quarterly Release</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Viral Diseases</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Presented positive results at the IDWeek conference from the Phase 3 double-blind, placebo-controlled trial (PINETREE) of Veklury administered intravenously in non-hospitalized COVID-19 patients at high risk for disease progression. Results demonstrated statistically significant reduction in risk for COVID-19 related hospitalization with Veklury compared with placebo.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Received Priority Review designations from FDA for the lenacapavir New Drug Applications (&#8220;NDAs&#8221;) for the treatment of HIV-1 infection in heavily treatment-experienced patients with multidrug resistance in combination with other antiretroviral agents. The NDAs have been granted a Prescription Drug User Fee Act action date of February 28, 2022</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Announced that the Marketing Authorization Application (&#8220;MAA&#8221;) for lenacapavir, an investigational, long-acting HIV-1 capsid inhibitor, was fully validated by European Medicines Agency (&#8220;EMA&#8221;). The proposed indication is for the treatment of HIV-1 infection, in combination with other antiretroviral(s), in adults with multidrug resistant HIV-1 infection who are currently on a failing antiretroviral treatment regimen due to resistance, intolerance or safety considerations.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Announced the initiation of the Phase 2 study evaluating an oral weekly combination of lenacapavir and islatravir in people who are living with HIV who are virologically suppressed on an antiretroviral therapy.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Began enrollment into the Phase 3 PURPOSE 1 trial in cisgender girls and young women, the second Phase 3 study of lenacapavir for HIV pre-exposure prophylaxis. The first Phase 3 study (PURPOSE 2) was initiated in July and is enrolling cisgender men, transgender men and women, and gender non-binary individuals who have sex with men.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Received FDA approval for the supplemental NDA of a new low-dose tablet form of Biktarvy (bictegravir 30mg&#47;FTC 120mg&#47;TAF 15mg), expanding the indication to include younger children weighing at least 14 kg to less than 25 kg who are virologically suppressed or new to antiretroviral therapy. Biktarvy (bictegravir 50mg&#47;FTC 200mg&#47;TAF 25mg) is approved for appropriate pediatric patients weighing at least 25 kg.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Oncology</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Announced the inclusion of Trodelvy into the National Comprehensive Cancer Network Guidelines for Breast Cancer as a preferred regimen for the treatment of adult patients with metastatic TNBC who received at least two prior therapies, with at least one for metastatic disease.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Received a positive opinion from the Committee for Medicinal Products for Human Use of the EMA for Trodelvy for the treatment of adults with unresectable or metastatic TNBC who have received two or more prior systemic therapies, at least one of them for advanced disease. The final European Commission decision is anticipated later in 2021. </font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Received approval from Health Canada for</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> Trodelvy for the treatment of adult patients with unresectable locally advanced or metastatic TNBC who have received two or more prior therapies, at least one of them for metastatic disease. Canada represents the fifth approval for Trodelvy in metastatic TNBC under the Project Orbis Initiative, following approvals in Australia, Great Britain, Switzerland, and the United States. </font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Presented sub-analyses</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> data from the Phase 3 ASCENT study evaluating Trodelvy in patients with relapsed or refractory metastatic TNBC at the European Society of Medical Oncology annual meeting. Results showed significant and clinically-meaningful improvements in health-related quality of life, and, in patients whose initial diagnosis was not TNBC but changed to triple-negative, Trodelvy demonstrated similar positive outcomes to the overall metastatic TNBC population. </font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Announced </font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">the submission of a supplemental Biologics License Application to </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">FDA for Yescarta to expand its current indication to include the treatment of adults with relapsed or refractory LBCL in the second-line setting. </font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div relapsed or refractory B-cell precursor acute lymphoblastic leukemia. </font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Announced a collaboration and license agreement with </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Appia Bio, Inc. </font><font directed toward hematological malignancies.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Announced that the company&#8217;s Board of Directors has declared a quarterly dividend of $0.71 per share of common stock for the fourth quarter of 2021. The dividend is payable on December 30, 2021, to stockholders of record at the close of business on December 15, 2021. Future dividends will be subject to Board approval.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font Indonesia and 3,000 vials to Armenia to help patients hospitalized with COVID-19.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Guidance and Outlook</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Gilead has updated its full-year guidance, and now expects&#58;</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Total product sales between $26.0 billion and $26.3 billion, compared to $24.4 billion and $25.0 billion previously, reflecting year-to-date results and our updated expectations for the fourth quarter 2021.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Total product sales, excluding Veklury, of approximately $21.5 billion, compared to $21.7 billion and $21.9 billion previously, primarily reflecting the longer than expected pandemic impact on our business.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Total Veklury sales between $4.5 billion and $4.8 billion, compared to $2.7 billion and $3.1 billion previously, primarily reflecting the surge in COVID-19 hospitalizations in the third quarter 2021, and our expectations for a significant step-down in hospitalization rates in the fourth quarter 2021.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">GAAP earnings per share between $5.50 and $5.70, compared to $4.70 and $5.05 previously.</font></div><div style="margin-top:3pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:12.53pt">Non-GAAP earnings per share between $7.90 and $8.10, compared to $6.90 and $7.25 previously.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">A reconciliation between GAAP and non-GAAP financial information for the 2021 guidance is provided in the accompanying tables. Also see the Forward-Looking Statements described below. The financial guidance is subject to a number of risks and uncertainties, including uncertainty around the duration and magnitude of the COVID-19 pandemic. While the pandemic can be expected to continue to impact Gilead&#8217;s business and broader market dynamics, the rate and degree of these impacts as well as the corresponding recovery from the pandemic may vary across Gilead&#8217;s business.</font></div><div style="height:36pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></div></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Non-GAAP Financial Information</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The information presented in this document has been prepared in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#8220;GAAP&#8221;), unless otherwise noted as non-GAAP. Management believes non-GAAP information is useful for investors, when considered in conjunction with Gilead&#8217;s GAAP financial information, because management uses such information internally for its operating, budgeting and financial planning purposes. Non-GAAP information is not prepared under a comprehensive set of accounting rules and should only be used to supplement an understanding of Gilead&#8217;s operating results as reported under GAAP. Non-GAAP financial information generally excludes acquisition-related expenses including amortization of acquired intangible assets and inventory step-up charges, acquired IPR&#38;D expenses, and other items that are considered unusual or not representative of underlying trends of Gilead&#8217;s business, fair value adjustments of equity securities and discrete and related tax charges or benefits associated with changes in tax related laws and guidelines. Acquired IPR&#38;D expenses reflect IPR&#38;D impairments as well as the initial costs of externally developed IPR&#38;D projects, acquired directly in a transaction other than a business combination, that do not have an alternative future use, including upfront and other payments related to various collaborations and the initial costs of rights to IPR&#38;D projects. Although Gilead consistently excludes the amortization of acquired intangible assets from the non-GAAP financial information, management believes that it is important for investors to understand that such intangible assets were recorded as part of acquisitions and contribute to ongoing revenue generation.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Non-GAAP measures may be defined and calculated differently by other companies in the same industry. Reconciliations of the non-GAAP financial measures to the most directly comparable GAAP financial measures are provided in the accompanying tables.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Conference Call</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">At 1&#58;30 p.m. Pacific Time today, Gilead will host a conference call to discuss Gilead&#8217;s results. A live webcast will be available on http&#58;&#47;&#47;investors.gilead.com and will be archived on www.gilead.com for one year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">About Gilead Sciences </font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Gilead Sciences, Inc. is a biopharmaceutical company that has pursued and achieved breakthroughs in medicine for more than three decades, with the goal of creating a healthier world for all people. The company is committed to advancing innovative medicines to prevent and treat life-threatening diseases, including HIV, viral hepatitis and cancer. Gilead operates in more than 35 countries worldwide, with headquarters in Foster City, California.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Forward-Looking Statements </font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Statements included in this press release that are not historical in nature are forward-looking statements within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}
